<p class="wikiPara">
<a href="http://beust.com/weblog/archives/000157.html" target="" class="regularLink">Cedric </a> and <a href="http://jboss.org/jbossBlog/blog/bburke/?permalink=XML+overrides+for+EJB3.html" target="" class="regularLink">Bill </a> have proposed solutions. My preference is basically similar to Bill's, but here's how I would write it:
</p>


<pre class="wikiPreformatted">
&lt;class name="org.hibernate.Item"&gt;
    @Entity
    @Table(name="AUCTION_ITEM")
    &lt;method sig="getBar()"&gt;@Transient&lt;/method&gt;
    &lt;method sig="doSomething(int, String)"&gt;
        @Tx(REQUIRES_NEW)
    &lt;/method&gt;
&lt;/class&gt;
</pre>


<p class="wikiPara">
I like this, because the same approach can be used outside of the context of J2EE. I /really/ wish something like this would have been included in JSR-175.
</p>
